Event.0: Apple Inc CEO Steve Jobs announces the iPhone
Event.1:
Election of Mahmoud Abbas
Mahmoud Abbas, who was a founder of Fatah in the 1950s and served briefly as prime minister of the Palestinian Authority (PA) in 2003 under Yāsir ʿArafāt, was elected president of the PA on this day in 2005.
Event.2: Michael Jackson receives the Artist of the Century award at the American music awards
Event.3: Apple introduced iTunes, a digital media player application that, with the year's later debut of the iPod, revolutionized digital music.
Event.4: Baseball officially bans Pete Rose from being elected to Hall of Fame for betting on baseball
Event.5: English earl of St Andrews marries Sylvana Tomaselli
Event.6: Sir Rudolph Bing (of NY Met Opera) marries Lady Carroll Douglass
Event.7: Catherine Middleton, who married (2011) Prince William and became the duchess of Cambridge, was born in Reading, Berkshire, England.
